    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="795"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d795">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>Your reply to our telegram as to Habana commissioners received. As we read
                    telegram of Wade to Adjutant-General it seems clear that our Cuban commissioners
                    undertook to discuss question of relinquishment of title and sovereignty and
                    advanced a proposition in relation thereto. We understood the protocol and their
                    instructions to restrict them to the military operation of evacuation, which was
                    to leave evacuated <pb facs="1020" n="924" xml:id="pg_924"/> places in military
                    occupation of United States. We understand that questions as to relinquishment
                    of title and sovereignty are committed to us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
